track_notes:
An attempt was made to Activate SS-102 then 115 and finally SS-162.

Due to the tree growth/plantations to the E/NE of these summits it was felt that it would be easier to locate a central point utilising the forest roads to avoid trying to navigate through these forest plantations. As the central location chosen involved over 12K of walking on top of the access distance to the top of the summits I used my MTB to cycle in and out to the end the track as shown where a small cottage is located.

With a change in the Wx on 115 and a delay whilst S2S chasing I decided to abandon SS-162 - it will still be there for another day.

Following on from my cycle access as described previously, and leaving my bike at NN390043, I followed the road towards Comer Farm striking off at a gated farm road at NN387042. From there into the fenced young forest heading upwards to access gate at NN389049 onto moor then on wards to SS-102 summit.
I utilised this route to drop down from SS-102 to the forest road then upwards to the summit of SS-115. Coming around the back-end of SS-115 as this route shows avoids the heavily cragged front.

Coming off SS-115 is tricky due to the crags to the S & SE sides of the mountain. As you descend it is difficult to see where crags end and could possibly get you into difficulty. I chose this more northern route. Once down at the forest road and looking up into these crags you can more easily see (if clear of mist) possible access routes which of course you could utilise as you descent.

Just remember this 2 pointer could catch you out in poor wx!!
track_title: SS-115 to MTB Drop-off Point - Activation 28th June 2014
